# F-1 & F-2 — complete the concurrent-writer re-sync fix (impl plan)

Extends PR #132. Source brief: `.claude/prompts/implement-f1-f2-resync-followups.md`.
Base: `origin/main` @ `a052285b` (contains PR #132's re-sync code). Worktree:
`.claude/worktrees/f1-f2-resync-followups`.

**Verified shapes (Explore + direct reads, 2026-05-23):**
- Handler `packages/ipc-core/src/handlers/workspace-commit-notify.ts`: export-baseline catch
  (143–179) already builds the envelope; **apply-bundle catch (290–311) returns a BARE veto.**
- `workspace-git-core/src/impl.ts` apply-bundle parent-mismatch: **Site 1 (1025–1032)** parent-CAS
  (`input.parent !== currentVersion`) — fires on a concurrent-writer advance; `currentVersion` is
  the freshly-read head. **Sites 2 (1045–1052) / 3 (1072–1079)** are post-CAS integrity checks
  (head already == parent there → NOT concurrent advances). None set `cause.actualParent`.
- `workspace-git-server/src/client/git-engine.ts` `parentMismatch` helper (898–910) already sets
  `cause.actualParent`; export path (1322–1332) sets both `actualParent` + `baselineBundleBytes`.
- `workspace-git-core` export-baseline-bundle (960–1006) does NOT strict-check head; with
  `{version: X}` it bundles AT X via `exportBundleAt` (rev-parse --verify) — so exporting at
  `actualParent` (the current head) succeeds and returns the bundle the runner needs.
- Runner per-turn loop `main.ts` 1006–1096 (verbatim captured); final commit 1191–1213 (only logs
  on `!accepted`). `MAX_RESYNC_ATTEMPTS=3` (1017). Client = `IpcClient` (`call<Action extends
  IpcActionName>(action, payload: unknown): Promise<unknown>`). `chat:turn-end` emits AFTER the
  loop (1121–1176) — must stay put.
- Tests cross-plugin import is allowed (eslint `no-restricted-imports` is OFF for
  `packages/*/src/**/__tests__/**`). `@ax/workspace-git-core` deps = @ax/core + isomorphic-git +
  picomatch (no cycle with ipc-core). Empty-baseline env in workspace-git-core impl.ts (48/85–94)
  is IDENTICAL to the server test's `SIM_BASELINE_ENV` (ax-runner / 1970 / fileMode=false) → OIDs
  line up.

---

## Task F-1 — apply-bundle catch forwards the re-sync envelope (single-replica backend)

Two production edits + one integration test. **TDD: write the test first (RED), then the edits.**

### F-1a — `workspace-git-core/src/impl.ts`: add `cause.actualParent` to the parent-CAS throw

ONLY **Site 1** (the parent-CAS at ~1025–1032). It's the genuine concurrent-writer detector
(`input.parent !== currentVersion`, where `currentVersion` is the freshly-read head). Leave Sites
2 and 3 bare — at both, `head === input.parent` already holds (no concurrent advance); they're
real bad-bundle/baseline vetoes, and forwarding `actualParent` there would trigger useless
resync-retries against the same head.

```ts
if (currentVersion !== null && input.parent !== currentVersion) {
  throw new PluginError({
    code: 'parent-mismatch',
    plugin: PLUGIN_NAME,
    hookName: 'workspace:apply-bundle',
    message: `expected parent ${currentVersion}, got ${input.parent === null ? 'null' : input.parent}`,
    // The freshly-read mirror head, so commit-notify can re-sync the runner
    // (mirror the multi-replica backend's parentMismatch contract). Sites 2/3
    // below are post-CAS integrity checks where head already == parent — not
    // concurrent advances — so they stay bare (no actualParent).
    cause: { actualParent: currentVersion },
  });
}
```

### F-1b — `workspace-commit-notify.ts`: apply-bundle catch forwards the envelope

Replace the bare apply-bundle catch (290–311). When the caught parent-mismatch carries
`actualParent` but no bundle (single-replica case), fetch a baseline bundle AT `actualParent` via
the **`workspace:export-baseline-bundle` hook** (NO direct backend import — invariant #2). Add a
small shared `resyncEnvelopeFromCause` helper and reuse it in the export catch too (DRY).

```ts
// module-scope helper (top of file)
function resyncEnvelopeFromCause(
  cause: unknown,
): { actualParent?: string; baselineBundleBytes?: string } {
  const out: { actualParent?: string; baselineBundleBytes?: string } = {};
  if (cause !== null && typeof cause === 'object') {
    const c = cause as Record<string, unknown>;
    if (typeof c.actualParent === 'string') out.actualParent = c.actualParent;
    if (typeof c.baselineBundleBytes === 'string') out.baselineBundleBytes = c.baselineBundleBytes;
  }
  return out;
}
```

Export catch (143–176) simplifies to use the helper. Apply-bundle catch becomes:

```ts
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof PluginError && err.code === 'parent-mismatch') {
    // A concurrent writer advanced the mirror past the runner's parent. On the
    // multi-replica backend the mismatch surfaces earlier (at export) WITH a
    // bundle; on the single-replica backend it surfaces HERE with only
    // actualParent. Fetch a baseline bundle AT that head (via the hook) so BOTH
    // backends return the full re-sync envelope instead of a bare veto.
    const env = resyncEnvelopeFromCause(err.cause);
    if (env.actualParent !== undefined && env.baselineBundleBytes === undefined) {
      try {
        const out = await bus.call<
          WorkspaceExportBaselineBundleInput,
          WorkspaceExportBaselineBundleOutput
        >('workspace:export-baseline-bundle', ctx, {
          version: env.actualParent as WorkspaceVersion,
        });
        env.baselineBundleBytes = out.bundleBytes;
      } catch (exportErr) {
        // Yet another writer advanced past actualParent between apply and
        // export. If export reports the fresher head+bundle, forward THAT;
        // otherwise fall back to a bare veto (runner rolls back this turn).
        if (exportErr instanceof PluginError && exportErr.code === 'parent-mismatch') {
          const fresher = resyncEnvelopeFromCause(exportErr.cause);
          if (fresher.actualParent !== undefined) env.actualParent = fresher.actualParent;
          if (fresher.baselineBundleBytes !== undefined) env.baselineBundleBytes = fresher.baselineBundleBytes;
        } else {
          logInternalError(ctx.logger, 'workspace.commit-notify', exportErr);
        }
      }
    }
    const body: Record<string, unknown> = {
      accepted: false as const,
      reason: `parent-mismatch: ${err.message}`,
    };
    // Only forward the PAIR — the runner ignores actualParent without a bundle.
    if (env.actualParent !== undefined && env.baselineBundleBytes !== undefined) {
      body.actualParent = env.actualParent;
      body.baselineBundleBytes = env.baselineBundleBytes;
    }
    const checked = WorkspaceCommitNotifyResponseSchema.safeParse(body);
    if (!checked.success) {
      logInternalError(ctx.logger, 'workspace.commit-notify',
        new Error(`response shape drift (apply-bundle parent-mismatch): ${checked.error.message}`));
      return internalError();
    }
    return { status: 200, body: checked.data };
  }
  throw err; // other errors → dispatcher catch-all (sanitized 500). UNCHANGED.
}
```

The runner side needs NO change — its existing loop already consumes this envelope.

